The paper focuses on using deep learning for computer vision tasks, specifically image segmentation and object recognition. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new encoder based on Voronoi Diagrams, which is related to geometric algorithms (cs.CG) and computational geometry (cs.GR). The paper also mentions using the proposed model for contour extraction and structure generation, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
